OL,4,CAmputee gets blue badge after 'leg will
OL,5,Cnot re-grow' letter
OL,6, A special constable who lost a leg in
OL,7, an accident has described his doctor as
OL,8, a "legend" for writing to the council
OL,9, after he was rejected for a blue badge.
OL,11,FBen Perry's right leg was amputated in
OL,12,F2018 after he was hit by a car.
OL,14,FHowever, when it came time to renew his
OL,15,Fblue badge, he said he was told he did
OL,16,Fnot qualify and was told to supply more
OL,17,Fevidence of his disability.
OL,19,FIn a letter, shared by Mr Perry on
OL,20,FTwitter, his doctor told the council
OL,21,Fhis leg was unlikely to "re-grow".
